==English==
=== Etymology ===
From {{Yidd.}} [[אױ גװאַלד]] ''(oy gvald).''  This comes from {{Pl}} [[gwałt]] ("violence", the Polish word has since gravitated into "rape").  On the other hand, in the usage of polish Jewry, the word was used for harm of any kind (including even being given an unfavourable price when haggling).

=== Interjection ===
[[Category:English interjections]]
'''oy gevalt'''!
# [[uh oh]]!
#:'''usage note:''' The expression is usually one of worry at the realization of negative consequences or the recognition of something that is adverse.